Well, there you have it. Please note than in some application
benchmarks, the performance of the system can equal or exceed
that of even a P5-100 (ie winbench graphics winmark, wintune
2.0). This is NOT to say that the system is as fast as those P5s
in every application, on the contrary, memory speed dependent
programs are almost always faster on a Pentium. I have maxed the
system to give me really good video/throughput performance for
little $$$s.

Finally, check AMD's BBS for a file called DMI.exe or some
such thing. It conatins excel spreadsheets with a variety of
benchmarks for the enhanced and non-enhanced AMD offerings of
various speeds. In addition, it has similar info for NexGen,
Cyrix, and Intel. AMD's web-site has abbreviated versions of
this.

